label.value: excess prospore membrane present

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which cells contain more prospore membrane than normal. Excess prospore membrane may take the form of bubble-like structures continuous with the rest of the membrane.

label.value: decreased phosphatidylinositol-3-phosphate binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of phosphatidylinositol-3-phosphate binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant is decreased. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

definition.value: This term can mean that the mutated gene product itself binds phosphatidylinositol-3-phosphate less than wild type, or that a mutation in one gene decreases phosphatidylinositol-3-phosphate binding by a second gene product. When using this term, it is therefore recommended to note the specific protein(s) affected.

label.value: abnormal mitochondrial RNA 3'-end processing

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mitochondrial RNA 3'-end processing is abnormal.

label.value: altered level of substance in mitochondrion

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of a specific substance measured in the mitochondrion differs from normal.

label.value: altered RNA level in mitochondrion

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA measured in the mitochondrion differs from normal.

label.value: normal level of substance in mitochondrion

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of a specific substance measured in the mitochondrion is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal mitochondrial RNA level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA measured in the mitochondria is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Total RNA or a specific RNA may be measured.

definition.value: We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein localization to chromatin at replication origin

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at replication origins is increased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to chromatin at replication origin

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at replication origins is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal plasma membrane sterol distribution

value.value: A localization phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the distribution of sterols in the plasma membrane is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: actin cortical patches present in decreased numbers

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells contain fewer actin cortical patches than normal.

label.value: inviable swollen pear-shaped vegetative cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a cell is inviable, is shaped in the form of a pear, and has a larger volume than normal, in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle. One end is rounded, while the other resembles an end of a normal rod-shaped cell. The normally shaped end has the same diameter as a wild-type cell.

label.value: increased duration of horsetail movement

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the duration of horsetail movement is longer than normal. Horsetail movement is the oscillatory movement of the nucleus that takes place during meiotic prophase I.

label.value: increased vegetative cell population growth during phosphate starvation

value.value: A cell growth phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is increased relative to normal under conditions of phosphate starvation.

label.value: decreased vegetative cell population growth during phosphate starvation

value.value: A cell growth phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is decreased relative to normal under conditions of phosphate starvation.

label.value: normal vegetative cell population growth during phosphate starvation

value.value: A cell growth phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) under conditions of phosphate starvation.

label.value: viable elongated vegetative cell during phosphate starvation

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a vegetative cell is viable and elongated when the cell is subject to phosphate starvation.

definition.value: Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'viable cell population' (FYPO:0002058) or one of its descendants.

label.value: decreased level of stress responsive gene mRNA during cellular response to phosphate starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of one or more messenger RNAs that are normally expressed during a cellular response to stress measured in a cell is lower than normal (i.e. lower than observed in wild-type cells during vegetative growth) during a cellular response to phosphate starvation.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription.

label.value: actin cortical patches present in increased numbers

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells contain more actin cortical patches than normal.

label.value: normal telomere localization

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which telomere localization, a process in which a telomere is transported to, and/or maintained in, a specific location, is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal telomere localization during mitotic interphase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which telomere localization, a process in which a telomere is transported to, and/or maintained in, a specific location, is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: decreased rate of microtubule depolymerization behind moving spindle pole body

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which depolymerization (i.e. removal of tubulin dimers) of microtubules extending behind a moving spindle pole body occurs at a lower rate, or speed, than normal.

label.value: increased rate of microtubule depolymerization ahead of moving spindle pole body

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which depolymerization (i.e. removal of tubulin dimers) of microtubules extending in front of a moving spindle pole body occurs at a greater rate, or speed, than normal.

label.value: increased protein localization to new cell tip

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to a new cell tip is increased.

definition.value: This term can apply to growing or non-growing new cell tips (i.e. before or after NETO), or both. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein localization to new growing cell tip

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to a new growing cell tip is increased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: elongated monoseptate vegetative cell

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a cell contains one septum, is longer than normal, and has a greater length:diameter ratio than normal.

label.value: decreased protein localization to eMTOC during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the equatorial microtubule organizing center is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal cellular histone level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of one or more histones measured in a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: increased centromeric transcript level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which RNAs transcribed from the centromeric region are present at greater levels than normal.

label.value: sensitive to vorinostat

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to vorinostat. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of vorinostat that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: decreased chromatin binding at centromere central core

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of chromatin binding by a gene product (usually a protein) at the central core of the centromeric regions is decreased.

label.value: entangled telomeres during vegetative growth

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells form telomeres that become entwined and resistant to separation.

label.value: abolished transcription during meiotic cell cycle

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which transcription does not occur during the meiotic cell cycle. All genes, or a specific subset of genes, may be affected.

label.value: sensitive to sunitinib

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to sunitinib. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of sunitinib that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: abnormal RNA level oscillation during mitotic cell cycle

value.value: A gene expression phenotype in which RNA levels that normally vary over the course of the mitotic cell cycle do not vary, or change in a pattern different from normal. Total RNA or a specific RNA, such as the mRNA transcribed from a gene of interest, may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal meiotic centromere clustering resulting in centromere-spindle pole body colocalization during prophase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which centromere clustering is abnormal during one or both meiotic nuclear divisions, such that one or more centromeres is associated with the spindle pole body (SPB) during prophase. Normally, centromeres and SPBs associate after prophase, but not earlier.

label.value: G2-exit meiosis with abolished premeiotic DNA replication

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which cells in the G2 phase of the mitotic cell cycle undergo meiotic nuclear divisions, and premeiotic DNA replication does not occur. In these cells, sister chromatids precociously segregate at the first meiotic nuclear division. Normally, upon nitrogen starvation cells arrest the mitotic cell in G1 phase, and then proceed into conjugation, premeiotic DNA replication and meiosis.

label.value: decreased protein level during meiotic cell cycle

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of protein measured in a cell during the meiotic cell cycle is lower than normal. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal translation or abnormal regulation of translation, but note that changes in protein levels may result from changes in protein stability or degradation as well as changes in protein synthesis. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein level during meiotic interphase

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of protein measured in a cell during interphase of the meiotic cell cycle is lower than normal. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal translation or abnormal regulation of translation, but note that changes in protein levels may result from changes in protein stability or degradation as well as changes in protein synthesis. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal spore germination frequency

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which spore germination occurs at a normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) frequency.

definition.value: Note that this phenotype is usually assayed by observing a population of spores and measuring how many germinate.

label.value: delayed onset of meiosis I

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the first meiotic nuclear division begins later than normal.

label.value: normal onset of meiosis I

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the first meiotic nuclear division begins at the normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) time relative to other cell cycle events.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to chromosome

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to a specific location on a chromosome is abnormal.

definition.value: Encompasses both presence of proteins not normally found at all or part of a chromosome and decreased levels or absence of proteins normally found there, and describes defects in a localization process. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to chromosome

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to a region in a chromosome is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased duration of horsetail movement

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the duration of horsetail movement is shorter than normal. Horsetail movement is the oscillatory movement of the nucleus that takes place during meiotic prophase I.

label.value: normal duration of horsetail movement

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the duration of horsetail movement is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Horsetail movement is the oscillatory movement of the nucleus that takes place during meiotic prophase I.

label.value: protein mislocalized to nucleus during mitotic interphase

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a protein that is not normally found in the nucleus is observed there during interphase of a mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: Note that this term can be used to annotate any case where a protein is found in the nucleus in a mutant, but not in wild type. In some cases, there may be enough additional information to annotate to 'abnormal protein localization' (FYPO:0000443) or one of its descendants. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased cellular HMW ubiquitin conjugate level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein having high molecular mass due to polyubiquitin conjugation is lower than normal.

label.value: elongated vegetative cell with oscillating nucleus

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell is elongated, and the nucleus undergoes oscillatory movement around its normal location.

label.value: abnormal protein complex composition

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which the composition of a protein complex differs from normal.

definition.value: For consistency with the GO cellular component ontology, 'protein complex' encompasses any complex that contains proteins, including ribonucleoprotein complexes, protein-DNA complexes, etc.
